fg_segments: ISTE Privacy Policy Notice ISTE is sincerely committed to protecting the privacy of our membership, as well as all others who come to our Web site in search of educational technology resources and information.
In order to better serve our constituency, we may collect certain types of data from those who visit the Web site:
IP Addresses and Server Information. We collect this to help monitor the performance of our systems, so that we can continue to improve our visitors' experience.
ISTE also uses a display advertising partner to collect visitor data on our site and then serve targeted display ads to you on other sites.
The techniques our partners employ do not collect personal information such as your name, email address, postal address or telephone number.
Our partners use technology such as cookies and web beacons to collect this data.
For more information or to opt-out of this type of advertising, please visit AdRoll's privacy policy.

Personal Information. We may request contact and other personal information in order to fulfill transactions, such as ISTE membership, the purchase of goods or services, registration for events, or to respond to requests for information.
We may also use your contact information to market ISTE products and services.
We reserve the right to share certain membership information with qualified third-party vendors for offerings that we determine to be of interest to our members.
If you'd rather not receive those offers, you may ask to be removed from any or all lists not directly related to our membership services by contacting our list manager:
List Manager 621 SW Morrison Street, Suite 800 Portland, OR 97205 USA E-mail: mailinglists@iste.org Phone: 503.342.2848 Fax: 503.882.0813
Please see our complete Privacy Policy under Legal Notices for more detailed information.

ISTE Privacy Policy Notice
ISTE is sincerely committed to protecting the privacy of our
membership, as well as all others who come to our Web site in search of educational technology resources and information. In order to better
serve our constituency, we may collect certain types of data from those
who visit the Web site:


IP Addresses and Server Information. We collect this to help monitor the performance of our systems, so that we can continue to improve our visitors’ experience. ISTE also uses a display advertising partner to collect visitor data on our site and then serve targeted display ads to you on other sites. The techniques our partners employ do not collect personal information such as your name, email address, postal address or telephone number. Our partners use technology such as cookies and web beacons to collect this data. For more information or to opt-out of this type of advertising, please visit AdRoll's privacy policy.
Personal Information. We may request contact and
    other personal information in order to fulfill transactions, such as
    ISTE membership, the purchase of goods or services, registration for
    events, or to respond to requests for information. We may also use your
    contact information to market ISTE products and services. We reserve the
    right to share certain membership information with qualified
    third-party vendors for offerings that we determine to be of interest to
    our members. If you'd rather not receive those offers, you may ask to
    be removed from any or all lists not directly related to our membership
    services by contacting our list manager:

   List Manager
621 SW Morrison Street, Suite 800
Portland, OR  97205 USA
E-mail: mailinglists@iste.org
Phone: 503.342.2848
Fax: 503.882.0813
  
Please see our complete Privacy Policy under Legal Notices for more detailed information.
